                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegrams.—Extracts.—Paraphrases.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 839.00/551.]</note>
                <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Santo Domingo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-04-15">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 15, 1912</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Government has a well equipped force in the field and could soon put down the
                    rebellion on the northwestern frontier were it not for the effective aid they
                    claim the Haitian Government is giving it. The Minister for Foreign Affairs is
                    anxious to know the attitude of our Government to the funding for the purchase
                    in the United States of a fast gunboat with a good battery; this, he says, would
                    greatly reduce the expenditures for maintaining peace.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Russell.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
